---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const pageTitle = "Privacy Policy | Infinity Metrics";
const pageDescription = "Read the Infinity Metrics privacy policy. Learn how our self-hosted, cookieless analytics protects user data and ensures compliance (GDPR, CCPA).";
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <Header />

  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12 max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-800">
      <p class="text-lg mb-8">Last updated: March 8, 2025</p>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Why We're Different</h2>
        <p>
          At Infinity Metrics ("we", "us", or "our"), privacy isn't an
          afterthought—it's the foundation. This policy covers how we handle
          data for both website owners (our customers) and their visitors
          (end-users). Here's the short version:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
          <li>No cookies. Ever.</li>
          <li>No personal data from visitors.</li>
          <li>No cross-site tracking.</li>
          <li>Self-hosted—you control everything.</li>
          <li>GDPR, CCPA, and privacy-law friendly by design.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We built Infinity Metrics to give you powerful insights without
          compromising anyone's privacy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">What We Collect</h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3">From You (Website Owners)</h3>
        <p>When you use Infinity Metrics, we collect:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
          <li>Your basics: name, email.</li>
          <li>
            Billing info (if applicable, handled by our secure payment
            processor).
          </li>
          <li>Website details where you install Infinity Metrics.</li>
          <li>Messages you send us.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3">From Visitors (End-Users)</h3>
        <p>The Infinity Metrics software collects:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
          <li>Anonymous stats: page views, referrers, browser type.</li>
          <li>Device info: type (mobile, tablet, desktop), OS, browser.</li>
          <li>Rough location: country only, nothing pinpoint.</li>
          <li>Session data: duration, pages visited, navigation paths.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <strong>Important:</strong> Since Infinity Metrics is self-hosted, all
          visitor data is collected and stored on <em>your</em> servers, not ours.
          We never have access to this data unless you explicitly share it with us
          for support purposes.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3">What We Skip</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
          <li>Personal info from visitors.</li>
          <li>Visitor IP addresses (hashed immediately and discarded).</li>
          <li>Fingerprinting that IDs individuals.</li>
          <li>Form inputs or content interactions.</li>
          <li>Anything from password-protected pages.</li>
          <li>Cross-site tracking.</li>
          <li>Persistent identifiers.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">How We Use It</h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3">For Website Owners</h3>
        <p>We use your info to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
          <li>Manage your license and release updates.</li>
          <li>Handle payments.</li>
          <li>Answer your questions and provide support.</li>
          <li>Build better features.</li>
          <li>Send occasional product updates and announcements.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3">For Visitors</h3>
        <p>Anonymous data helps website owners:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
          <li>Understand site traffic and usage patterns.</li>
          <li>Identify popular content and referral sources.</li>
          <li>Optimize site performance and user experience.</li>
          <li><strong>Never</strong>: profile individuals or target ads.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Where Your Data Lives</h2>
        <p>
          Infinity Metrics is self-hosted, all visitor analytics data is stored
          on your own servers. That means:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
          <li>Visitor data stays with you, not us.</li>
          <li>It's in a database you control.</li>
          <li>
            We never see or access your analytics data unless you explicitly
            share it for support purposes.
          </li>
          <li>
            We secure data in transit; you're responsible for securing your
            server and database.
          </li>
          <li>You control data retention policies and backups.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Your account information (name, email, etc.) is stored securely on our
          servers to manage your subscription and provide customer service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Who Sees Your Data</h2>
        <p>We don't sell or share your info, period. Exceptions:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
          <li>
            Trusted partners (like payment processors) who help us run things.
          </li>
          <li>Legal requirements or to protect our rights.</li>
          <li>A business sale (with your okay).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Visitor analytics data is stored exclusively on your servers. We don't
          have access to it unless you explicitly share it with us for support
          purposes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Your Control</h2>
        <p>As a website owner, you can:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
          <li>Edit or delete your account info, just ask.</li>
          <li>Skip marketing emails (service updates stay).</li>
          <li>Request what data we have on you.</li>
          <li>Delete all analytics data from your servers at any time.</li>
          <li>Configure data retention policies however you prefer.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>As a visitor to a site using Infinity Metrics:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
          <li>No personal data is collected = nothing to delete.</li>
          <li>No cookies = no cookie consent banners needed.</li>
          <li>Block JavaScript or use privacy tools if you want.</li>
          <li>
            Contact the site owner with privacy concerns about their analytics
            practices.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">GDPR & Global Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          We've designed Infinity Metrics to help website owners stay compliant
          with privacy laws worldwide. Read more in <a
            href="/gdpr"
            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">our GDPR guide</a
          >
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">
          Self-Hosted Privacy Responsibilities
        </h2>
        <p>
          Please refer to our <a
            href="/terms"
            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Terms of Service</a
          >
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Updates to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We might update this policy periodically. Check the "Last updated"
          date at the top. For significant changes, we'll notify you via email
          or through our website.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
